33static void rename(GlobalValue *GV) { GV->setName(GV->getName() + ".old"); }
34
35// Upgrade the declarations of the SSE4.1 ptest intrinsics whose arguments have
36// changed their type from v4f32 to v2i64.
37static bool UpgradePTESTIntrinsic(Function* F, Intrinsic::ID IID,
38 Function *&NewFn) {
39 // Check whether this is an old version of the function, which received
40 // v4f32 arguments.
41 Type *Arg0Type = F->getFunctionType()->getParamType(0);
42 if (Arg0Type != VectorType::get(Type::getFloatTy(F->getContext()), 4))
43 return false;
44
45 // Yes, it's old, replace it with new version.
46 rename(F);
47 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), IID);
48 return true;
49}
50
51// Upgrade the declarations of intrinsic functions whose 8-bit immediate mask
52// arguments have changed their type from i32 to i8.
53static bool UpgradeX86IntrinsicsWith8BitMask(Function *F, Intrinsic::ID IID,
54 Function *&NewFn) {
55 // Check that the last argument is an i32.
56 Type *LastArgType = F->getFunctionType()->getParamType(
57 F->getFunctionType()->getNumParams() - 1);
58 if (!LastArgType->isIntegerTy(32))
59 return false;
60
61 // Move this function aside and map down.
62 rename(F);
63 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), IID);
64 return true;
65}

358 Name.startswith("avx512.mask.valign.") || // Added in 4.0
359 Name.startswith("sse2.psll.dq") || // Added in 3.7
360 Name.startswith("sse2.psrl.dq") || // Added in 3.7
361 Name.startswith("avx2.psll.dq") || // Added in 3.7
362 Name.startswith("avx2.psrl.dq") || // Added in 3.7
363 Name.startswith("avx512.psll.dq") || // Added in 3.9
364 Name.startswith("avx512.psrl.dq") || // Added in 3.9
365 Name == "sse41.pblendw" || // Added in 3.7
366 Name.startswith("sse41.blendp") || // Added in 3.7
367 Name.startswith("avx.blend.p") || // Added in 3.7
368 Name == "avx2.pblendw" || // Added in 3.7
369 Name.startswith("avx2.pblendd.") || // Added in 3.7
370 Name.startswith("avx.vbroadcastf128") || // Added in 4.0
371 Name == "avx2.vbroadcasti128" || // Added in 3.7
372 Name.startswith("avx512.mask.broadcastf") || // Added in 6.0
373 Name.startswith("avx512.mask.broadcasti") || // Added in 6.0
374 Name == "xop.vpcmov" || // Added in 3.8
375 Name == "xop.vpcmov.256" || // Added in 5.0
376 Name.startswith("avx512.mask.move.s") || // Added in 4.0
377 Name.startswith("avx512.cvtmask2") || // Added in 5.0
378 Name.startswith("xop.vpcom") || // Added in 3.2, Updated in 9.0
379 Name.startswith("xop.vprot") || // Added in 8.0
380 Name.startswith("avx512.prol") || // Added in 8.0
381 Name.startswith("avx512.pror") || // Added in 8.0
382 Name.startswith("avx512.mask.prorv.") || // Added in 8.0
383 Name.startswith("avx512.mask.pror.") || // Added in 8.0
384 Name.startswith("avx512.mask.prolv.") || // Added in 8.0
385 Name.startswith("avx512.mask.prol.") || // Added in 8.0
386 Name.startswith("avx512.ptestm") || //Added in 6.0
387 Name.startswith("avx512.ptestnm") || //Added in 6.0
388 Name.startswith("avx512.mask.pavg")) // Added in 6.0
389 return true;
390
391 return false;
392}

394static bool UpgradeX86IntrinsicFunction(Function *F, StringRef Name,
395 Function *&NewFn) {
396 // Only handle intrinsics that start with "x86.".
397 if (!Name.startswith("x86."))
398 return false;
399 // Remove "x86." prefix.
400 Name = Name.substr(4);
401
402 if (ShouldUpgradeX86Intrinsic(F, Name)) {
403 NewFn = nullptr;
404 return true;
405 }
406
407 if (Name == "rdtscp") { // Added in 8.0
408 // If this intrinsic has 0 operands, it's the new version.
409 if (F->getFunctionType()->getNumParams() == 0)
410 return false;
411
412 rename(F);
413 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(),
414 Intrinsic::x86_rdtscp);
415 return true;
416 }
417
418 // SSE4.1 ptest functions may have an old signature.
419 if (Name.startswith("sse41.ptest")) { // Added in 3.2
420 if (Name.substr(11) == "c")
421 return UpgradePTESTIntrinsic(F, Intrinsic::x86_sse41_ptestc, NewFn);
422 if (Name.substr(11) == "z")
423 return UpgradePTESTIntrinsic(F, Intrinsic::x86_sse41_ptestz, NewFn);
424 if (Name.substr(11) == "nzc")
425 return UpgradePTESTIntrinsic(F, Intrinsic::x86_sse41_ptestnzc, NewFn);
426 }
427 // Several blend and other instructions with masks used the wrong number of
428 // bits.
429 if (Name == "sse41.insertps") // Added in 3.6
430 return UpgradeX86IntrinsicsWith8BitMask(F, Intrinsic::x86_sse41_insertps,
431 NewFn);
432 if (Name == "sse41.dppd") // Added in 3.6
433 return UpgradeX86IntrinsicsWith8BitMask(F, Intrinsic::x86_sse41_dppd,
434 NewFn);
435 if (Name == "sse41.dpps") // Added in 3.6
436 return UpgradeX86IntrinsicsWith8BitMask(F, Intrinsic::x86_sse41_dpps,
437 NewFn);
438 if (Name == "sse41.mpsadbw") // Added in 3.6
439 return UpgradeX86IntrinsicsWith8BitMask(F, Intrinsic::x86_sse41_mpsadbw,
440 NewFn);
441 if (Name == "avx.dp.ps.256") // Added in 3.6
442 return UpgradeX86IntrinsicsWith8BitMask(F, Intrinsic::x86_avx_dp_ps_256,
443 NewFn);
444 if (Name == "avx2.mpsadbw") // Added in 3.6
445 return UpgradeX86IntrinsicsWith8BitMask(F, Intrinsic::x86_avx2_mpsadbw,
446 NewFn);
447
448 // frcz.ss/sd may need to have an argument dropped. Added in 3.2
449 if (Name.startswith("xop.vfrcz.ss") && F->arg_size() == 2) {
450 rename(F);
451 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(),
452 Intrinsic::x86_xop_vfrcz_ss);
453 return true;
454 }
455 if (Name.startswith("xop.vfrcz.sd") && F->arg_size() == 2) {
456 rename(F);
457 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(),
458 Intrinsic::x86_xop_vfrcz_sd);
459 return true;
460 }
461 // Upgrade any XOP PERMIL2 index operand still using a float/double vector.
462 if (Name.startswith("xop.vpermil2")) { // Added in 3.9
463 auto Idx = F->getFunctionType()->getParamType(2);
464 if (Idx->isFPOrFPVectorTy()) {
465 rename(F);
466 unsigned IdxSize = Idx->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
467 unsigned EltSize = Idx->getScalarSizeInBits();
468 Intrinsic::ID Permil2ID;
469 if (EltSize == 64 && IdxSize == 128)
470 Permil2ID = Intrinsic::x86_xop_vpermil2pd;
471 else if (EltSize == 32 && IdxSize == 128)
472 Permil2ID = Intrinsic::x86_xop_vpermil2ps;
473 else if (EltSize == 64 && IdxSize == 256)
474 Permil2ID = Intrinsic::x86_xop_vpermil2pd_256;
475 else
476 Permil2ID = Intrinsic::x86_xop_vpermil2ps_256;
477 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), Permil2ID);
478 return true;
479 }
480 }
481
482 if (Name == "seh.recoverfp") {
483 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), Intrinsic::eh_recoverfp);
484 return true;
485 }
486
487 return false;
488}
489
490static bool UpgradeIntrinsicFunction1(Function *F, Function *&NewFn) {
491 assert(F && "Illegal to upgrade a non-existent Function.");
492
493 // Upgrade intrinsics "clang.arc.use" which doesn't start with "llvm.".
494 if (F->getName() == "clang.arc.use") {
495 NewFn = nullptr;
496 return true;
497 }
498
499 // Quickly eliminate it, if it's not a candidate.
500 StringRef Name = F->getName();
501 if (Name.size() <= 8 || !Name.startswith("llvm."))
502 return false;
503 Name = Name.substr(5); // Strip off "llvm."
504
505 switch (Name[0]) {
506 default: break;
507 case 'a': {
508 if (Name == "addressofreturnaddress") {
509 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(),
510 Intrinsic::addressofreturnaddress,
511 F->getReturnType());
512 return true;
513 }
514
515 if (Name.startswith("arm.rbit") || Name.startswith("aarch64.rbit")) {
516 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), Intrinsic::bitreverse,
517 F->arg_begin()->getType());
518 return true;
519 }
520 if (Name.startswith("arm.neon.vclz")) {
521 Type* args[2] = {
522 F->arg_begin()->getType(),
523 Type::getInt1Ty(F->getContext())
524 };
525 // Can't use Intrinsic::getDeclaration here as it adds a ".i1" to
526 // the end of the name. Change name from llvm.arm.neon.vclz.* to
527 // llvm.ctlz.*
528 FunctionType* fType = FunctionType::get(F->getReturnType(), args, false);
529 NewFn = Function::Create(fType, F->getLinkage(), F->getAddressSpace(),
530 "llvm.ctlz." + Name.substr(14), F->getParent());
531 return true;
532 }
533 if (Name.startswith("arm.neon.vcnt")) {
534 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), Intrinsic::ctpop,
535 F->arg_begin()->getType());
536 return true;
537 }
538 Regex vldRegex("^arm\\.neon\\.vld([1234]|[234]lane)\\.v[a-z0-9]*$");
539 if (vldRegex.match(Name)) {
540 auto fArgs = F->getFunctionType()->params();
541 SmallVector<Type *, 4> Tys(fArgs.begin(), fArgs.end());
542 // Can't use Intrinsic::getDeclaration here as the return types might
543 // then only be structurally equal.
544 FunctionType* fType = FunctionType::get(F->getReturnType(), Tys, false);
545 NewFn = Function::Create(fType, F->getLinkage(), F->getAddressSpace(),
546 "llvm." + Name + ".p0i8", F->getParent());
547 return true;
548 }
549 Regex vstRegex("^arm\\.neon\\.vst([1234]|[234]lane)\\.v[a-z0-9]*$");
550 if (vstRegex.match(Name)) {
551 static const Intrinsic::ID StoreInts[] = {Intrinsic::arm_neon_vst1,
552 Intrinsic::arm_neon_vst2,
553 Intrinsic::arm_neon_vst3,
554 Intrinsic::arm_neon_vst4};
555
556 static const Intrinsic::ID StoreLaneInts[] = {
557 Intrinsic::arm_neon_vst2lane, Intrinsic::arm_neon_vst3lane,
558 Intrinsic::arm_neon_vst4lane
559 };
560
561 auto fArgs = F->getFunctionType()->params();
562 Type *Tys[] = {fArgs[0], fArgs[1]};
563 if (Name.find("lane") == StringRef::npos)
564 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(),
565 StoreInts[fArgs.size() - 3], Tys);
566 else
567 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(),
568 StoreLaneInts[fArgs.size() - 5], Tys);
569 return true;
570 }
571 if (Name == "aarch64.thread.pointer" || Name == "arm.thread.pointer") {
572 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), Intrinsic::thread_pointer);
573 return true;
574 }
575 if (Name.startswith("aarch64.neon.addp")) {
576 if (F->arg_size() != 2)
577 break; // Invalid IR.
578 auto fArgs = F->getFunctionType()->params();
579 VectorType *ArgTy = dyn_cast<VectorType>(fArgs[0]);
580 if (ArgTy && ArgTy->getElementType()->isFloatingPointTy()) {
581 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(),
582 Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_faddp, fArgs);
583 return true;
584 }
585 }
586 if (Name == "annotation") {
587 Type *Tys[] = {F->getReturnType(), F->getFunctionType()->params()[1] };
588 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), Intrinsic::annotation, Tys);
589 return true;
590 }
591 break;
592 }
593
594 case 'c': {
595 if (Name.startswith("ctlz.") && F->arg_size() == 1) {
596 rename(F);
597 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), Intrinsic::ctlz,
598 F->arg_begin()->getType());
599 return true;
600 }
601 if (Name.startswith("cttz.") && F->arg_size() == 1) {
602 rename(F);
603 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), Intrinsic::cttz,
604 F->arg_begin()->getType());
605 return true;
606 }
607 break;
608 }
609 case 'd': {
610 if (Name == "dbg.value" && F->arg_size() == 4) {
611 rename(F);
612 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), Intrinsic::dbg_value);
613 return true;
614 }
615 break;
616 }
617 case 'f':
618 if (Name == "frameaddress") {
619 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), Intrinsic::frameaddress,
620 F->getReturnType());
621 return true;
622 }
623 break;
624 case 'e': {
625 SmallVector<StringRef, 2> Groups;
626 Regex R("^experimental.vector.reduce.([a-z]+)\\.[fi][0-9]+");
627 if (R.match(Name, &Groups)) {
628 Intrinsic::ID ID = Intrinsic::not_intrinsic;
629 if (Groups[1] == "fadd")
630 ID = Intrinsic::experimental_vector_reduce_v2_fadd;
631 if (Groups[1] == "fmul")
632 ID = Intrinsic::experimental_vector_reduce_v2_fmul;
633
634 if (ID != Intrinsic::not_intrinsic) {
635 rename(F);
636 auto Args = F->getFunctionType()->params();
637 Type *Tys[] = {F->getFunctionType()->getReturnType(), Args[1]};
638 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), ID, Tys);
639 return true;
640 }
641 }
642 break;
643 }
644 case 'i':
645 case 'l': {
646 bool IsLifetimeStart = Name.startswith("lifetime.start");
647 if (IsLifetimeStart || Name.startswith("invariant.start")) {
648 Intrinsic::ID ID = IsLifetimeStart ?
649 Intrinsic::lifetime_start : Intrinsic::invariant_start;
650 auto Args = F->getFunctionType()->params();
651 Type* ObjectPtr[1] = {Args[1]};
652 if (F->getName() != Intrinsic::getName(ID, ObjectPtr)) {
653 rename(F);
654 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), ID, ObjectPtr);
655 return true;
656 }
657 }
658
659 bool IsLifetimeEnd = Name.startswith("lifetime.end");
660 if (IsLifetimeEnd || Name.startswith("invariant.end")) {
661 Intrinsic::ID ID = IsLifetimeEnd ?
662 Intrinsic::lifetime_end : Intrinsic::invariant_end;
663
664 auto Args = F->getFunctionType()->params();
665 Type* ObjectPtr[1] = {Args[IsLifetimeEnd ? 1 : 2]};
666 if (F->getName() != Intrinsic::getName(ID, ObjectPtr)) {
667 rename(F);
668 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), ID, ObjectPtr);
669 return true;
670 }
671 }
672 if (Name.startswith("invariant.group.barrier")) {
673 // Rename invariant.group.barrier to launder.invariant.group
674 auto Args = F->getFunctionType()->params();
675 Type* ObjectPtr[1] = {Args[0]};
676 rename(F);
677 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(),
678 Intrinsic::launder_invariant_group, ObjectPtr);
679 return true;
680
681 }
682
683 break;
684 }
685 case 'm': {
686 if (Name.startswith("masked.load.")) {
687 Type *Tys[] = { F->getReturnType(), F->arg_begin()->getType() };
688 if (F->getName() != Intrinsic::getName(Intrinsic::masked_load, Tys)) {
689 rename(F);
690 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(),
691 Intrinsic::masked_load,
692 Tys);
693 return true;
694 }
695 }
696 if (Name.startswith("masked.store.")) {
697 auto Args = F->getFunctionType()->params();
698 Type *Tys[] = { Args[0], Args[1] };
699 if (F->getName() != Intrinsic::getName(Intrinsic::masked_store, Tys)) {
700 rename(F);
701 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(),
702 Intrinsic::masked_store,
703 Tys);
704 return true;
705 }
706 }
707 // Renaming gather/scatter intrinsics with no address space overloading
708 // to the new overload which includes an address space
709 if (Name.startswith("masked.gather.")) {
710 Type *Tys[] = {F->getReturnType(), F->arg_begin()->getType()};
711 if (F->getName() != Intrinsic::getName(Intrinsic::masked_gather, Tys)) {
712 rename(F);
713 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(),
714 Intrinsic::masked_gather, Tys);
715 return true;
716 }
717 }
718 if (Name.startswith("masked.scatter.")) {
719 auto Args = F->getFunctionType()->params();
720 Type *Tys[] = {Args[0], Args[1]};
721 if (F->getName() != Intrinsic::getName(Intrinsic::masked_scatter, Tys)) {
722 rename(F);
723 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(),
724 Intrinsic::masked_scatter, Tys);
725 return true;
726 }
727 }
728 // Updating the memory intrinsics (memcpy/memmove/memset) that have an
729 // alignment parameter to embedding the alignment as an attribute of
730 // the pointer args.
731 if (Name.startswith("memcpy.") && F->arg_size() == 5) {
732 rename(F);
733 // Get the types of dest, src, and len
734 ArrayRef<Type *> ParamTypes = F->getFunctionType()->params().slice(0, 3);
735 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), Intrinsic::memcpy,
736 ParamTypes);
737 return true;
738 }
739 if (Name.startswith("memmove.") && F->arg_size() == 5) {
740 rename(F);
741 // Get the types of dest, src, and len
742 ArrayRef<Type *> ParamTypes = F->getFunctionType()->params().slice(0, 3);
743 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), Intrinsic::memmove,
744 ParamTypes);
745 return true;
746 }
747 if (Name.startswith("memset.") && F->arg_size() == 5) {
748 rename(F);
749 // Get the types of dest, and len
750 const auto *FT = F->getFunctionType();
751 Type *ParamTypes[2] = {
752 FT->getParamType(0), // Dest
753 FT->getParamType(2) // len
754 };
755 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), Intrinsic::memset,
756 ParamTypes);
757 return true;
758 }
759 break;
760 }
761 case 'n': {
762 if (Name.startswith("nvvm.")) {
763 Name = Name.substr(5);
764
765 // The following nvvm intrinsics correspond exactly to an LLVM intrinsic.
766 Intrinsic::ID IID = StringSwitch<Intrinsic::ID>(Name)
767 .Cases("brev32", "brev64", Intrinsic::bitreverse)
768 .Case("clz.i", Intrinsic::ctlz)
769 .Case("popc.i", Intrinsic::ctpop)
770 .Default(Intrinsic::not_intrinsic);
771 if (IID != Intrinsic::not_intrinsic && F->arg_size() == 1) {
772 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), IID,
773 {F->getReturnType()});
774 return true;
775 }
776
777 // The following nvvm intrinsics correspond exactly to an LLVM idiom, but
778 // not to an intrinsic alone. We expand them in UpgradeIntrinsicCall.
779 //
780 // TODO: We could add lohi.i2d.
781 bool Expand = StringSwitch<bool>(Name)
782 .Cases("abs.i", "abs.ll", true)
783 .Cases("clz.ll", "popc.ll", "h2f", true)
784 .Cases("max.i", "max.ll", "max.ui", "max.ull", true)
785 .Cases("min.i", "min.ll", "min.ui", "min.ull", true)
786 .Default(false);
787 if (Expand) {
788 NewFn = nullptr;
789 return true;
790 }
791 }
792 break;
793 }
794 case 'o':
795 // We only need to change the name to match the mangling including the
796 // address space.
797 if (Name.startswith("objectsize.")) {
798 Type *Tys[2] = { F->getReturnType(), F->arg_begin()->getType() };
799 if (F->arg_size() == 2 || F->arg_size() == 3 ||
800 F->getName() != Intrinsic::getName(Intrinsic::objectsize, Tys)) {
801 rename(F);
802 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), Intrinsic::objectsize,
803 Tys);
804 return true;
805 }
806 }
807 break;
808 case 'p':
809 if (Name == "ptr.annotation") {
810 Type *Tys[] = {F->getReturnType(), F->getFunctionType()->params()[1] };
811 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(),
812 Intrinsic::ptr_annotation, Tys);
813 return true;
814 }
815 break;
816 case 'r':
817 if (Name == "returnaddress") {
818 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(
819 F->getParent(), Intrinsic::returnaddress, F->getReturnType());
820 return true;
821 }
822 break;
823 case 's':
824 if (Name == "stackprotectorcheck") {
825 NewFn = nullptr;
826 return true;
827 }
828 if (Name == "stacksave") {
829 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), Intrinsic::stacksave,
830 F->getReturnType());
831 return true;
832 }
833 if (Name == "stackrestore") {
834 auto *ArgTy = F->arg_begin()->getType();
835 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), Intrinsic::stackrestore,
836 ArgTy);
837 return true;
838 }
839 break;
840
841 case 'v': {
842 auto *ArgTy = F->arg_begin()->getType();
843 if (Name == "va_start") {
844 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), Intrinsic::vastart,
845 ArgTy);
846 return true;
847 }
848 if (Name == "va_end") {
849 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), Intrinsic::vaend,
850 ArgTy);
851 return true;
852 }
853 if (Name == "va_copy") {
854 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), Intrinsic::vacopy,
855 { ArgTy, ArgTy });
856 return true;
857 }
858 if (Name == "var.annotation") {
859 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(),
860 Intrinsic::var_annotation, ArgTy);
861 return true;
862 }
863 break;
864 }
865
866 case 'x':
867 if (UpgradeX86IntrinsicFunction(F, Name, NewFn))
868 return true;
869 }
870 // Remangle our intrinsic since we upgrade the mangling
871 auto Result = llvm::Intrinsic::remangleIntrinsicFunction(F);
872 if (Result != None) {
873 NewFn = Result.getValue();
874 return true;
875 }
876
877 // This may not belong here. This function is effectively being overloaded
878 // to both detect an intrinsic which needs upgrading, and to provide the
879 // upgraded form of the intrinsic. We should perhaps have two separate
880 // functions for this.
881 return false;
882}
883
884bool llvm::UpgradeIntrinsicFunction(Function *F, Function *&NewFn) {
885 NewFn = nullptr;
886 bool Upgraded = UpgradeIntrinsicFunction1(F, NewFn);
887 assert(F != NewFn && "Intrinsic function upgraded to the same function");
888
889 // Upgrade intrinsic attributes. This does not change the function.
890 if (NewFn)
891 F = NewFn;
892 if (Intrinsic::ID id = F->getIntrinsicID())
893 F->setAttributes(Intrinsic::getAttributes(F->getContext(), id));
894 return Upgraded;
895}
896
897GlobalVariable *llvm::UpgradeGlobalVariable(GlobalVariable *GV) {
898 if (!(GV->hasName() && (GV->getName() == "llvm.global_ctors" ||
899 GV->getName() == "llvm.global_dtors")) ||
900 !GV->hasInitializer())
901 return nullptr;
902 ArrayType *ATy = dyn_cast<ArrayType>(GV->getValueType());
903 if (!ATy)
904 return nullptr;
905 StructType *STy = dyn_cast<StructType>(ATy->getElementType());
906 if (!STy || STy->getNumElements() != 2)
907 return nullptr;
908
909 LLVMContext &C = GV->getContext();
910 IRBuilder<> IRB(C);
911 auto EltTy = StructType::get(STy->getElementType(0), STy->getElementType(1),
912 IRB.getInt8PtrTy());
913 Constant *Init = GV->getInitializer();
914 unsigned N = Init->getNumOperands();
915 std::vector<Constant *> NewCtors(N);
916 for (unsigned i = 0; i != N; ++i) {
917 auto Ctor = cast<Constant>(Init->getOperand(i));
918 NewCtors[i] = ConstantStruct::get(
919 EltTy, Ctor->getAggregateElement(0u), Ctor->getAggregateElement(1),
920 Constant::getNullValue(IRB.getInt8PtrTy()));
921 }
922 Constant *NewInit = ConstantArray::get(ArrayType::get(EltTy, N), NewCtors);
923
924 return new GlobalVariable(NewInit->getType(), false, GV->getLinkage(),
925 NewInit, GV->getName());
926}
927
928// Handles upgrading SSE2/AVX2/AVX512BW PSLLDQ intrinsics by converting them
929// to byte shuffles.
930static Value *UpgradeX86PSLLDQIntrinsics(IRBuilder<> &Builder,
931 Value *Op, unsigned Shift) {
932 Type *ResultTy = Op->getType();
933 unsigned NumElts = ResultTy->getVectorNumElements() * 8;
934
935 // Bitcast from a 64-bit element type to a byte element type.
936 Type *VecTy = VectorType::get(Builder.getInt8Ty(), NumElts);
937 Op = Builder.CreateBitCast(Op, VecTy, "cast");
938
939 // We'll be shuffling in zeroes.
940 Value *Res = Constant::getNullValue(VecTy);
941
942 // If shift is less than 16, emit a shuffle to move the bytes. Otherwise,
943 // we'll just return the zero vector.
944 if (Shift < 16) {
945 uint32_t Idxs[64];
946 // 256/512-bit version is split into 2/4 16-byte lanes.
947 for (unsigned l = 0; l != NumElts; l += 16)
948 for (unsigned i = 0; i != 16; ++i) {
949 unsigned Idx = NumElts + i - Shift;
950 if (Idx < NumElts)
951 Idx -= NumElts - 16; // end of lane, switch operand.
952 Idxs[l + i] = Idx + l;
953 }
954
955 Res = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Res, Op, makeArrayRef(Idxs, NumElts));
956 }
957
958 // Bitcast back to a 64-bit element type.
959 return Builder.CreateBitCast(Res, ResultTy, "cast");
960}
961
962// Handles upgrading SSE2/AVX2/AVX512BW PSRLDQ intrinsics by converting them
963// to byte shuffles.
964static Value *UpgradeX86PSRLDQIntrinsics(IRBuilder<> &Builder, Value *Op,
965 unsigned Shift) {
966 Type *ResultTy = Op->getType();
967 unsigned NumElts = ResultTy->getVectorNumElements() * 8;
968
969 // Bitcast from a 64-bit element type to a byte element type.
970 Type *VecTy = VectorType::get(Builder.getInt8Ty(), NumElts);
971 Op = Builder.CreateBitCast(Op, VecTy, "cast");
972
973 // We'll be shuffling in zeroes.
974 Value *Res = Constant::getNullValue(VecTy);
975
976 // If shift is less than 16, emit a shuffle to move the bytes. Otherwise,
977 // we'll just return the zero vector.
978 if (Shift < 16) {
979 uint32_t Idxs[64];
980 // 256/512-bit version is split into 2/4 16-byte lanes.
981 for (unsigned l = 0; l != NumElts; l += 16)
982 for (unsigned i = 0; i != 16; ++i) {
983 unsigned Idx = i + Shift;
984 if (Idx >= 16)
985 Idx += NumElts - 16; // end of lane, switch operand.
986 Idxs[l + i] = Idx + l;
987 }
988
989 Res = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Op, Res, makeArrayRef(Idxs, NumElts));
990 }
991
992 // Bitcast back to a 64-bit element type.
993 return Builder.CreateBitCast(Res, ResultTy, "cast");
994}
995
996static Value *getX86MaskVec(IRBuilder<> &Builder, Value *Mask,
997 unsigned NumElts) {
998 llvm::VectorType *MaskTy = llvm::VectorType::get(Builder.getInt1Ty(),
999 cast<IntegerType>(Mask->getType())->getBitWidth());
1000 Mask = Builder.CreateBitCast(Mask, MaskTy);
1001
1002 // If we have less than 8 elements, then the starting mask was an i8 and
1003 // we need to extract down to the right number of elements.
1004 if (NumElts < 8) {
1005 uint32_t Indices[4];
1006 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i)
1007 Indices[i] = i;
1008 Mask = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Mask, Mask,
1009 makeArrayRef(Indices, NumElts),
1010 "extract");
1011 }
1012
1013 return Mask;
1014}

1016static Value *EmitX86Select(IRBuilder<> &Builder, Value *Mask,
1017 Value *Op0, Value *Op1) {
1018 // If the mask is all ones just emit the first operation.
1019 if (const auto *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(Mask))
1020 if (C->isAllOnesValue())
1021 return Op0;
1022
1023 Mask = getX86MaskVec(Builder, Mask, Op0->getType()->getVectorNumElements());
1024 return Builder.CreateSelect(Mask, Op0, Op1);
1025}
1026
1027static Value *EmitX86ScalarSelect(IRBuilder<> &Builder, Value *Mask,
1028 Value *Op0, Value *Op1) {
1029 // If the mask is all ones just emit the first operation.
1030 if (const auto *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(Mask))
1031 if (C->isAllOnesValue())
1032 return Op0;
1033
1034 llvm::VectorType *MaskTy =
1035 llvm::VectorType::get(Builder.getInt1Ty(),
1036 Mask->getType()->getIntegerBitWidth());
1037 Mask = Builder.CreateBitCast(Mask, MaskTy);
1038 Mask = Builder.CreateExtractElement(Mask, (uint64_t)0);
1039 return Builder.CreateSelect(Mask, Op0, Op1);
1040}
1041
1042// Handle autoupgrade for masked PALIGNR and VALIGND/Q intrinsics.
1043// PALIGNR handles large immediates by shifting while VALIGN masks the immediate
1044// so we need to handle both cases. VALIGN also doesn't have 128-bit lanes.
1045static Value *UpgradeX86ALIGNIntrinsics(IRBuilder<> &Builder, Value *Op0,
1046 Value *Op1, Value *Shift,
1047 Value *Passthru, Value *Mask,
1048 bool IsVALIGN) {
1049 unsigned ShiftVal = cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(Shift)->getZExtValue();
1050
1051 unsigned NumElts = Op0->getType()->getVectorNumElements();
1052 assert((IsVALIGN || NumElts % 16 == 0) && "Illegal NumElts for PALIGNR!");
1053 assert((!IsVALIGN || NumElts <= 16) && "NumElts too large for VALIGN!");
1054 assert(isPowerOf2_32(NumElts) && "NumElts not a power of 2!");
1055
1056 // Mask the immediate for VALIGN.
1057 if (IsVALIGN)
1058 ShiftVal &= (NumElts - 1);
1059
1060 // If palignr is shifting the pair of vectors more than the size of two
1061 // lanes, emit zero.
1062 if (ShiftVal >= 32)
1063 return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(Op0->getType());
1064
1065 // If palignr is shifting the pair of input vectors more than one lane,
1066 // but less than two lanes, convert to shifting in zeroes.
1067 if (ShiftVal > 16) {
1068 ShiftVal -= 16;
1069 Op1 = Op0;
1070 Op0 = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(Op0->getType());
1071 }
1072
1073 uint32_t Indices[64];
1074 // 256-bit palignr operates on 128-bit lanes so we need to handle that
1075 for (unsigned l = 0; l < NumElts; l += 16) {
1076 for (unsigned i = 0; i != 16; ++i) {
1077 unsigned Idx = ShiftVal + i;
1078 if (!IsVALIGN && Idx >= 16) // Disable wrap for VALIGN.
1079 Idx += NumElts - 16; // End of lane, switch operand.
1080 Indices[l + i] = Idx + l;
1081 }
1082 }
1083
1084 Value *Align = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Op1, Op0,
1085 makeArrayRef(Indices, NumElts),
1086 "palignr");
1087
1088 return EmitX86Select(Builder, Mask, Align, Passthru);
1089}

1091static Value *UpgradeX86VPERMT2Intrinsics(IRBuilder<> &Builder, CallInst &CI,
1092 bool ZeroMask, bool IndexForm) {
1093 Type *Ty = CI.getType();
1094 unsigned VecWidth = Ty->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
1095 unsigned EltWidth = Ty->getScalarSizeInBits();
1096 bool IsFloat = Ty->isFPOrFPVectorTy();
1097 Intrinsic::ID IID;
1098 if (VecWidth == 128 && EltWidth == 32 && IsFloat)
1099 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_ps_128;
1100 else if (VecWidth == 128 && EltWidth == 32 && !IsFloat)
1101 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_d_128;
1102 else if (VecWidth == 128 && EltWidth == 64 && IsFloat)
1103 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_pd_128;
1104 else if (VecWidth == 128 && EltWidth == 64 && !IsFloat)
1105 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_q_128;
1106 else if (VecWidth == 256 && EltWidth == 32 && IsFloat)
1107 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_ps_256;
1108 else if (VecWidth == 256 && EltWidth == 32 && !IsFloat)
1109 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_d_256;
1110 else if (VecWidth == 256 && EltWidth == 64 && IsFloat)
1111 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_pd_256;
1112 else if (VecWidth == 256 && EltWidth == 64 && !IsFloat)
1113 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_q_256;
1114 else if (VecWidth == 512 && EltWidth == 32 && IsFloat)
1115 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_ps_512;
1116 else if (VecWidth == 512 && EltWidth == 32 && !IsFloat)
1117 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_d_512;
1118 else if (VecWidth == 512 && EltWidth == 64 && IsFloat)
1119 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_pd_512;
1120 else if (VecWidth == 512 && EltWidth == 64 && !IsFloat)
1121 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_q_512;
1122 else if (VecWidth == 128 && EltWidth == 16)
1123 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_hi_128;
1124 else if (VecWidth == 256 && EltWidth == 16)
1125 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_hi_256;
1126 else if (VecWidth == 512 && EltWidth == 16)
1127 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_hi_512;
1128 else if (VecWidth == 128 && EltWidth == 8)
1129 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_qi_128;
1130 else if (VecWidth == 256 && EltWidth == 8)
1131 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_qi_256;
1132 else if (VecWidth == 512 && EltWidth == 8)
1133 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_qi_512;
1134 else
1135 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected intrinsic");
1136
1137 Value *Args[] = { CI.getArgOperand(0) , CI.getArgOperand(1),
1138 CI.getArgOperand(2) };
1139
1140 // If this isn't index form we need to swap operand 0 and 1.
1141 if (!IndexForm)
1142 std::swap(Args[0], Args[1]);
1143
1144 Value *V = Builder.CreateCall(Intrinsic::getDeclaration(CI.getModule(), IID),
1145 Args);
1146 Value *PassThru = ZeroMask ? ConstantAggregateZero::get(Ty)
1147 : Builder.CreateBitCast(CI.getArgOperand(1),
1148 Ty);
1149 return EmitX86Select(Builder, CI.getArgOperand(3), V, PassThru);
1150}

1152static Value *UpgradeX86AddSubSatIntrinsics(IRBuilder<> &Builder, CallInst &CI,
1153 bool IsSigned, bool IsAddition) {
1154 Type *Ty = CI.getType();
1155 Value *Op0 = CI.getOperand(0);
1156 Value *Op1 = CI.getOperand(1);
1157
1158 Intrinsic::ID IID =
1159 IsSigned ? (IsAddition ? Intrinsic::sadd_sat : Intrinsic::ssub_sat)
1160 : (IsAddition ? Intrinsic::uadd_sat : Intrinsic::usub_sat);
1161 Function *Intrin = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(CI.getModule(), IID, Ty);
1162 Value *Res = Builder.CreateCall(Intrin, {Op0, Op1});
1163
1164 if (CI.getNumArgOperands() == 4) { // For masked intrinsics.
1165 Value *VecSrc = CI.getOperand(2);
1166 Value *Mask = CI.getOperand(3);
1167 Res = EmitX86Select(Builder, Mask, Res, VecSrc);
1168 }
1169 return Res;
1170}

1172static Value *upgradeX86Rotate(IRBuilder<> &Builder, CallInst &CI,
1173 bool IsRotateRight) {
1174 Type *Ty = CI.getType();
1175 Value *Src = CI.getArgOperand(0);
1176 Value *Amt = CI.getArgOperand(1);
1177
1178 // Amount may be scalar immediate, in which case create a splat vector.
1179 // Funnel shifts amounts are treated as modulo and types are all power-of-2 so
1180 // we only care about the lowest log2 bits anyway.
1181 if (Amt->getType() != Ty) {
1182 unsigned NumElts = Ty->getVectorNumElements();
1183 Amt = Builder.CreateIntCast(Amt, Ty->getScalarType(), false);
1184 Amt = Builder.CreateVectorSplat(NumElts, Amt);
1185 }
1186
1187 Intrinsic::ID IID = IsRotateRight ? Intrinsic::fshr : Intrinsic::fshl;
1188 Function *Intrin = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(CI.getModule(), IID, Ty);
1189 Value *Res = Builder.CreateCall(Intrin, {Src, Src, Amt});
1190
1191 if (CI.getNumArgOperands() == 4) { // For masked intrinsics.
1192 Value *VecSrc = CI.getOperand(2);
1193 Value *Mask = CI.getOperand(3);
1194 Res = EmitX86Select(Builder, Mask, Res, VecSrc);
1195 }
1196 return Res;
1197}

1199static Value *upgradeX86vpcom(IRBuilder<> &Builder, CallInst &CI, unsigned Imm,
1200 bool IsSigned) {
1201 Type *Ty = CI.getType();
1202 Value *LHS = CI.getArgOperand(0);
1203 Value *RHS = CI.getArgOperand(1);
1204
1205 CmpInst::Predicate Pred;
1206 switch (Imm) {
1207 case 0x0:
1208 Pred = IsSigned ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT : ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT;
1209 break;
1210 case 0x1:
1211 Pred = IsSigned ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE : ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE;
1212 break;
1213 case 0x2:
1214 Pred = IsSigned ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT : ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT;
1215 break;
1216 case 0x3:
1217 Pred = IsSigned ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE : ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE;
1218 break;
1219 case 0x4:
1220 Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ;
1221 break;
1222 case 0x5:
1223 Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_NE;
1224 break;
1225 case 0x6:
1226 return Constant::getNullValue(Ty); // FALSE
1227 case 0x7:
1228 return Constant::getAllOnesValue(Ty); // TRUE
1229 default:
1230 llvm_unreachable("Unknown XOP vpcom/vpcomu predicate");
1231 }
1232
1233 Value *Cmp = Builder.CreateICmp(Pred, LHS, RHS);
1234 Value *Ext = Builder.CreateSExt(Cmp, Ty);
1235 return Ext;
1236}

1238static Value *upgradeX86ConcatShift(IRBuilder<> &Builder, CallInst &CI,
1239 bool IsShiftRight, bool ZeroMask) {
1240 Type *Ty = CI.getType();
1241 Value *Op0 = CI.getArgOperand(0);
1242 Value *Op1 = CI.getArgOperand(1);
1243 Value *Amt = CI.getArgOperand(2);
1244
1245 if (IsShiftRight)
1246 std::swap(Op0, Op1);
1247
1248 // Amount may be scalar immediate, in which case create a splat vector.
1249 // Funnel shifts amounts are treated as modulo and types are all power-of-2 so
1250 // we only care about the lowest log2 bits anyway.
1251 if (Amt->getType() != Ty) {
1252 unsigned NumElts = Ty->getVectorNumElements();
1253 Amt = Builder.CreateIntCast(Amt, Ty->getScalarType(), false);
1254 Amt = Builder.CreateVectorSplat(NumElts, Amt);
1255 }
1256
1257 Intrinsic::ID IID = IsShiftRight ? Intrinsic::fshr : Intrinsic::fshl;
1258 Function *Intrin = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(CI.getModule(), IID, Ty);
1259 Value *Res = Builder.CreateCall(Intrin, {Op0, Op1, Amt});
1260
1261 unsigned NumArgs = CI.getNumArgOperands();
1262 if (NumArgs >= 4) { // For masked intrinsics.
1263 Value *VecSrc = NumArgs == 5 ? CI.getArgOperand(3) :
1264 ZeroMask ? ConstantAggregateZero::get(CI.getType()) :
1265 CI.getArgOperand(0);
1266 Value *Mask = CI.getOperand(NumArgs - 1);
1267 Res = EmitX86Select(Builder, Mask, Res, VecSrc);
1268 }
1269 return Res;
1270}

1272static Value *UpgradeMaskedStore(IRBuilder<> &Builder,
1273 Value *Ptr, Value *Data, Value *Mask,
1274 bool Aligned) {
1275 // Cast the pointer to the right type.
1276 Ptr = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ptr,
1277 llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(Data->getType()));
1278 unsigned Align =
1279 Aligned ? cast<VectorType>(Data->getType())->getBitWidth() / 8 : 1;
1280
1281 // If the mask is all ones just emit a regular store.
1282 if (const auto *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(Mask))
1283 if (C->isAllOnesValue())
1284 return Builder.CreateAlignedStore(Data, Ptr, Align);
1285
1286 // Convert the mask from an integer type to a vector of i1.
1287 unsigned NumElts = Data->getType()->getVectorNumElements();
1288 Mask = getX86MaskVec(Builder, Mask, NumElts);
1289 return Builder.CreateMaskedStore(Data, Ptr, Align, Mask);
1290}

1292static Value *UpgradeMaskedLoad(IRBuilder<> &Builder,
1293 Value *Ptr, Value *Passthru, Value *Mask,
1294 bool Aligned) {
1295 Type *ValTy = Passthru->getType();
1296 // Cast the pointer to the right type.
1297 Ptr = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ptr, llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(ValTy));
1298 unsigned Align =
1299 Aligned ? cast<VectorType>(Passthru->getType())->getBitWidth() / 8 : 1;
1300
1301 // If the mask is all ones just emit a regular store.
1302 if (const auto *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(Mask))
1303 if (C->isAllOnesValue())
1304 return Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(ValTy, Ptr, Align);
1305
1306 // Convert the mask from an integer type to a vector of i1.
1307 unsigned NumElts = Passthru->getType()->getVectorNumElements();
1308 Mask = getX86MaskVec(Builder, Mask, NumElts);
1309 return Builder.CreateMaskedLoad(Ptr, Align, Mask, Passthru);
1310}

1312static Value *upgradeAbs(IRBuilder<> &Builder, CallInst &CI) {
1313 Value *Op0 = CI.getArgOperand(0);
1314 llvm::Type *Ty = Op0->getType();
1315 Value *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(Ty);
1316 Value *Cmp = Builder.CreateICmp(ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT, Op0, Zero);
1317 Value *Neg = Builder.CreateNeg(Op0);
1318 Value *Res = Builder.CreateSelect(Cmp, Op0, Neg);
1319
1320 if (CI.getNumArgOperands() == 3)
1321 Res = EmitX86Select(Builder,CI.getArgOperand(2), Res, CI.getArgOperand(1));
1322
1323 return Res;
1324}

1339static Value *upgradePMULDQ(IRBuilder<> &Builder, CallInst &CI, bool IsSigned) {
1340 Type *Ty = CI.getType();
1341
1342 // Arguments have a vXi32 type so cast to vXi64.
1343 Value *LHS = Builder.CreateBitCast(CI.getArgOperand(0), Ty);
1344 Value *RHS = Builder.CreateBitCast(CI.getArgOperand(1), Ty);
1345
1346 if (IsSigned) {
1347 // Shift left then arithmetic shift right.
1348 Constant *ShiftAmt = ConstantInt::get(Ty, 32);
1349 LHS = Builder.CreateShl(LHS, ShiftAmt);
1350 LHS = Builder.CreateAShr(LHS, ShiftAmt);
1351 RHS = Builder.CreateShl(RHS, ShiftAmt);
1352 RHS = Builder.CreateAShr(RHS, ShiftAmt);
1353 } else {
1354 // Clear the upper bits.
1355 Constant *Mask = ConstantInt::get(Ty, 0xffffffff);
1356 LHS = Builder.CreateAnd(LHS, Mask);
1357 RHS = Builder.CreateAnd(RHS, Mask);
1358 }
1359
1360 Value *Res = Builder.CreateMul(LHS, RHS);
1361
1362 if (CI.getNumArgOperands() == 4)
1363 Res = EmitX86Select(Builder, CI.getArgOperand(3), Res, CI.getArgOperand(2));
1364
1365 return Res;
1366}

1368// Applying mask on vector of i1's and make sure result is at least 8 bits wide.
1369static Value *ApplyX86MaskOn1BitsVec(IRBuilder<> &Builder, Value *Vec,
1370 Value *Mask) {
1371 unsigned NumElts = Vec->getType()->getVectorNumElements();
1372 if (Mask) {
1373 const auto *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(Mask);
1374 if (!C || !C->isAllOnesValue())
1375 Vec = Builder.CreateAnd(Vec, getX86MaskVec(Builder, Mask, NumElts));
1376 }
1377
1378 if (NumElts < 8) {
1379 uint32_t Indices[8];
1380 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i)
1381 Indices[i] = i;
1382 for (unsigned i = NumElts; i != 8; ++i)
1383 Indices[i] = NumElts + i % NumElts;
1384 Vec = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Vec,
1385 Constant::getNullValue(Vec->getType()),
1386 Indices);
1387 }
1388 return Builder.CreateBitCast(Vec, Builder.getIntNTy(std::max(NumElts, 8U)));
1389}

1391static Value *upgradeMaskedCompare(IRBuilder<> &Builder, CallInst &CI,
1392 unsigned CC, bool Signed) {
1393 Value *Op0 = CI.getArgOperand(0);
1394 unsigned NumElts = Op0->getType()->getVectorNumElements();
1395
1396 Value *Cmp;
1397 if (CC == 3) {
1398 Cmp = Constant::getNullValue(llvm::VectorType::get(Builder.getInt1Ty(), NumElts));
1399 } else if (CC == 7) {
1400 Cmp = Constant::getAllOnesValue(llvm::VectorType::get(Builder.getInt1Ty(), NumElts));
1401 } else {
1402 ICmpInst::Predicate Pred;
1403 switch (CC) {
1404 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown condition code");
1405 case 0: Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ; break;
1406 case 1: Pred = Signed ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT : ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT; break;
1407 case 2: Pred = Signed ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE : ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE; break;
1408 case 4: Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_NE; break;
1409 case 5: Pred = Signed ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE : ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE; break;
1410 case 6: Pred = Signed ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT : ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT; break;
1411 }
1412 Cmp = Builder.CreateICmp(Pred, Op0, CI.getArgOperand(1));
1413 }
1414
1415 Value *Mask = CI.getArgOperand(CI.getNumArgOperands() - 1);
1416
1417 return ApplyX86MaskOn1BitsVec(Builder, Cmp, Mask);
1418}

1427}

1429static Value* upgradeMaskedMove(IRBuilder<> &Builder, CallInst &CI) {
1430 Value* A = CI.getArgOperand(0);
1431 Value* B = CI.getArgOperand(1);
1432 Value* Src = CI.getArgOperand(2);
1433 Value* Mask = CI.getArgOperand(3);
1434
1435 Value* AndNode = Builder.CreateAnd(Mask, APInt(8, 1));
1436 Value* Cmp = Builder.CreateIsNotNull(AndNode);
1437 Value* Extract1 = Builder.CreateExtractElement(B, (uint64_t)0);
1438 Value* Extract2 = Builder.CreateExtractElement(Src, (uint64_t)0);
1439 Value* Select = Builder.CreateSelect(Cmp, Extract1, Extract2);
1440 return Builder.CreateInsertElement(A, Select, (uint64_t)0);
1441}

1452// Replace intrinsic with unmasked version and a select.
1453static bool upgradeAVX512MaskToSelect(StringRef Name, IRBuilder<> &Builder,
1454 CallInst &CI, Value *&Rep) {
1455 Name = Name.substr(12); // Remove avx512.mask.
1456
1457 unsigned VecWidth = CI.getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
1458 unsigned EltWidth = CI.getType()->getScalarSizeInBits();
1459 Intrinsic::ID IID;
1460 if (Name.startswith("max.p")) {
1461 if (VecWidth == 128 && EltWidth == 32)
1462 IID = Intrinsic::x86_sse_max_ps;
1463 else if (VecWidth == 128 && EltWidth == 64)
1464 IID = Intrinsic::x86_sse2_max_pd;
1465 else if (VecWidth == 256 && EltWidth == 32)
1466 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx_max_ps_256;
1467 else if (VecWidth == 256 && EltWidth == 64)
1468 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx_max_pd_256;
1469 else
1470 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected intrinsic");
1471 } else if (Name.startswith("min.p")) {
1472 if (VecWidth == 128 && EltWidth == 32)
1473 IID = Intrinsic::x86_sse_min_ps;
1474 else if (VecWidth == 128 && EltWidth == 64)
1475 IID = Intrinsic::x86_sse2_min_pd;
1476 else if (VecWidth == 256 && EltWidth == 32)
1477 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx_min_ps_256;
1478 else if (VecWidth == 256 && EltWidth == 64)
1479 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx_min_pd_256;

1692/// Upgrade comment in call to inline asm that represents an objc retain release
1693/// marker.
1694void llvm::UpgradeInlineAsmString(std::string *AsmStr) {
1695 size_t Pos;
1696 if (AsmStr->find("mov\tfp") == 0 &&
1697 AsmStr->find("objc_retainAutoreleaseReturnValue") != std::string::npos &&
1698 (Pos = AsmStr->find("# marker")) != std::string::npos) {
1699 AsmStr->replace(Pos, 1, ";");
1700 }
1701 return;
1702}

1704/// Upgrade a call to an old intrinsic. All argument and return casting must be
1705/// provided to seamlessly integrate with existing context.
1706void llvm::UpgradeIntrinsicCall(CallInst *CI, Function *NewFn) {
1707 Function *F = CI->getCalledFunction();
1708 LLVMContext &C = CI->getContext();
1709 IRBuilder<> Builder(C);
1710 Builder.SetInsertPoint(CI->getParent(), CI->getIterator());
1711
1712 assert(F && "Intrinsic call is not direct?");
1713
1714 if (!NewFn) {
1715 // Get the Function's name.
1716 StringRef Name = F->getName();
1717
1718 // clang.arc.use is an old name for llvm.arc.clang.arc.use. It is dropped
1719 // from upgrader because the optimizer now only recognizes intrinsics for
1720 // ARC runtime calls.
1721 if (Name == "clang.arc.use") {
1722 CI->eraseFromParent();
1723 return;
1724 }
1725
1726 assert(Name.startswith("llvm.") && "Intrinsic doesn't start with 'llvm.'");
1727 Name = Name.substr(5);
1728
1729 bool IsX86 = Name.startswith("x86.");
1730 if (IsX86)
1731 Name = Name.substr(4);
1732 bool IsNVVM = Name.startswith("nvvm.");
1733 if (IsNVVM)
1734 Name = Name.substr(5);
1735
1736 if (IsX86 && Name.startswith("sse4a.movnt.")) {
1737 Module *M = F->getParent();
1738 SmallVector<Metadata *, 1> Elts;
1739 Elts.push_back(
1740 ConstantAsMetadata::get(ConstantInt::get(Type::getInt32Ty(C), 1)));
1741 MDNode *Node = MDNode::get(C, Elts);
1742
1743 Value *Arg0 = CI->getArgOperand(0);
1744 Value *Arg1 = CI->getArgOperand(1);
1745
1746 // Nontemporal (unaligned) store of the 0'th element of the float/double
1747 // vector.
1748 Type *SrcEltTy = cast<VectorType>(Arg1->getType())->getElementType();
1749 PointerType *EltPtrTy = PointerType::getUnqual(SrcEltTy);
1750 Value *Addr = Builder.CreateBitCast(Arg0, EltPtrTy, "cast");
1751 Value *Extract =
1752 Builder.CreateExtractElement(Arg1, (uint64_t)0, "extractelement");
1753
1754 StoreInst *SI = Builder.CreateAlignedStore(Extract, Addr, 1);
1755 SI->setMetadata(M->getMDKindID("nontemporal"), Node);
1756
1757 // Remove intrinsic.
1758 CI->eraseFromParent();
1759 return;
1760 }
1761
1762 if (IsX86 && (Name.startswith("avx.movnt.") ||
1763 Name.startswith("avx512.storent."))) {
1764 Module *M = F->getParent();
1765 SmallVector<Metadata *, 1> Elts;
1766 Elts.push_back(
1767 ConstantAsMetadata::get(ConstantInt::get(Type::getInt32Ty(C), 1)));
1768 MDNode *Node = MDNode::get(C, Elts);
1769
1770 Value *Arg0 = CI->getArgOperand(0);
1771 Value *Arg1 = CI->getArgOperand(1);
1772
1773 // Convert the type of the pointer to a pointer to the stored type.
1774 Value *BC = Builder.CreateBitCast(Arg0,
1775 PointerType::getUnqual(Arg1->getType()),
1776 "cast");
1777 VectorType *VTy = cast<VectorType>(Arg1->getType());
1778 StoreInst *SI = Builder.CreateAlignedStore(Arg1, BC,
1779 VTy->getBitWidth() / 8);
1780 SI->setMetadata(M->getMDKindID("nontemporal"), Node);
1781
1782 // Remove intrinsic.
1783 CI->eraseFromParent();
1784 return;
1785 }
1786
1787 if (IsX86 && Name == "sse2.storel.dq") {
1788 Value *Arg0 = CI->getArgOperand(0);
1789 Value *Arg1 = CI->getArgOperand(1);
1790
1791 Type *NewVecTy = VectorType::get(Type::getInt64Ty(C), 2);
1792 Value *BC0 = Builder.CreateBitCast(Arg1, NewVecTy, "cast");
1793 Value *Elt = Builder.CreateExtractElement(BC0, (uint64_t)0);
1794 Value *BC = Builder.CreateBitCast(Arg0,
1795 PointerType::getUnqual(Elt->getType()),
1796 "cast");
1797 Builder.CreateAlignedStore(Elt, BC, 1);
1798
1799 // Remove intrinsic.
1800 CI->eraseFromParent();
1801 return;
1802 }
1803
1804 if (IsX86 && (Name.startswith("sse.storeu.") ||
1805 Name.startswith("sse2.storeu.") ||
1806 Name.startswith("avx.storeu."))) {
1807 Value *Arg0 = CI->getArgOperand(0);
1808 Value *Arg1 = CI->getArgOperand(1);
1809
1810 Arg0 = Builder.CreateBitCast(Arg0,
1811 PointerType::getUnqual(Arg1->getType()),
1812 "cast");
1813 Builder.CreateAlignedStore(Arg1, Arg0, 1);
1814
1815 // Remove intrinsic.
1816 CI->eraseFromParent();
1817 return;
1818 }
1819
1820 if (IsX86 && Name == "avx512.mask.store.ss") {
1821 Value *Mask = Builder.CreateAnd(CI->getArgOperand(2), Builder.getInt8(1));
1822 UpgradeMaskedStore(Builder, CI->getArgOperand(0), CI->getArgOperand(1),
1823 Mask, false);
1824
1825 // Remove intrinsic.
1826 CI->eraseFromParent();
1827 return;
1828 }
1829
1830 if (IsX86 && (Name.startswith("avx512.mask.store"))) {
1831 // "avx512.mask.storeu." or "avx512.mask.store."
1832 bool Aligned = Name[17] != 'u'; // "avx512.mask.storeu".
1833 UpgradeMaskedStore(Builder, CI->getArgOperand(0), CI->getArgOperand(1),
1834 CI->getArgOperand(2), Aligned);
1835
1836 // Remove intrinsic.
1837 CI->eraseFromParent();
1838 return;
1839 }
1840
1841 Value *Rep;
1842 // Upgrade packed integer vector compare intrinsics to compare instructions.
1843 if (IsX86 && (Name.startswith("sse2.pcmp") ||
1844 Name.startswith("avx2.pcmp"))) {
1845 // "sse2.pcpmpeq." "sse2.pcmpgt." "avx2.pcmpeq." or "avx2.pcmpgt."
1846 bool CmpEq = Name[9] == 'e';
1847 Rep = Builder.CreateICmp(CmpEq ? ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ : ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT,
1848 CI->getArgOperand(0), CI->getArgOperand(1));
1849 Rep = Builder.CreateSExt(Rep, CI->getType(), "");
1850 } else if (IsX86 && (Name.startswith("avx512.broadcastm"))) {
1851 Type *ExtTy = Type::getInt32Ty(C);
1852 if (CI->getOperand(0)->getType()->isIntegerTy(8))
1853 ExtTy = Type::getInt64Ty(C);
1854 unsigned NumElts = CI->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits() /
1855 ExtTy->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
1856 Rep = Builder.CreateZExt(CI->getArgOperand(0), ExtTy);
1857 Rep = Builder.CreateVectorSplat(NumElts, Rep);
1858 } else if (IsX86 && (Name == "sse.sqrt.ss" ||
1859 Name == "sse2.sqrt.sd")) {
1860 Value *Vec = CI->getArgOperand(0);
1861 Value *Elt0 = Builder.CreateExtractElement(Vec, (uint64_t)0);
1862 Function *Intr = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(),
1863 Intrinsic::sqrt, Elt0->getType());
1864 Elt0 = Builder.CreateCall(Intr, Elt0);
1865 Rep = Builder.CreateInsertElement(Vec, Elt0, (uint64_t)0);
1866 } else if (IsX86 && (Name.startswith("avx.sqrt.p") ||
1867 Name.startswith("sse2.sqrt.p") ||
1868 Name.startswith("sse.sqrt.p"))) {
1869 Rep = Builder.CreateCall(Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(),
1870 Intrinsic::sqrt,
1871 CI->getType()),
1872 {CI->getArgOperand(0)});
1873 } else if (IsX86 && (Name.startswith("avx512.mask.sqrt.p"))) {
1874 if (CI->getNumArgOperands() == 4 &&
1875 (!isa<ConstantInt>(CI->getArgOperand(3)) ||
1876 cast<ConstantInt>(CI->getArgOperand(3))->getZExtValue() != 4)) {
1877 Intrinsic::ID IID = Name[18] == 's' ? Intrinsic::x86_avx512_sqrt_ps_512
1878 : Intrinsic::x86_avx512_sqrt_pd_512;
1879
1880 Value *Args[] = { CI->getArgOperand(0), CI->getArgOperand(3) };
1881 Rep = Builder.CreateCall(Intrinsic::getDeclaration(CI->getModule(),
1882 IID), Args);
1883 } else {
1884 Rep = Builder.CreateCall(Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(),
1885 Intrinsic::sqrt,
1886 CI->getType()),
1887 {CI->getArgOperand(0)});
1888 }
1889 Rep = EmitX86Select(Builder, CI->getArgOperand(2), Rep,
1890 CI->getArgOperand(1));
1891 } else if (IsX86 && (Name.startswith("avx512.ptestm") ||
1892 Name.startswith("avx512.ptestnm"))) {
1893 Value *Op0 = CI->getArgOperand(0);
1894 Value *Op1 = CI->getArgOperand(1);
1895 Value *Mask = CI->getArgOperand(2);
1896 Rep = Builder.CreateAnd(Op0, Op1);
1897 llvm::Type *Ty = Op0->getType();
1898 Value *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(Ty);
1899 ICmpInst::Predicate Pred =
1900 Name.startswith("avx512.ptestm") ? ICmpInst::ICMP_NE : ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ;
1901 Rep = Builder.CreateICmp(Pred, Rep, Zero);
1902 Rep = ApplyX86MaskOn1BitsVec(Builder, Rep, Mask);
1903 } else if (IsX86 && (Name.startswith("avx512.mask.pbroadcast"))){
1904 unsigned NumElts =
1905 CI->getArgOperand(1)->getType()->getVectorNumElements();
1906 Rep = Builder.CreateVectorSplat(NumElts, CI->getArgOperand(0));
1907 Rep = EmitX86Select(Builder, CI->getArgOperand(2), Rep,
1908 CI->getArgOperand(1));
1909 } else if (IsX86 && (Name.startswith("avx512.kunpck"))) {
1910 unsigned NumElts = CI->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits();
1911 Value *LHS = getX86MaskVec(Builder, CI->getArgOperand(0), NumElts);
1912 Value *RHS = getX86MaskVec(Builder, CI->getArgOperand(1), NumElts);
1913 uint32_t Indices[64];
1914 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i)
1915 Indices[i] = i;
1916
1917 // First extract half of each vector. This gives better codegen than
1918 // doing it in a single shuffle.
1919 LHS = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(LHS, LHS,
1920 makeArrayRef(Indices, NumElts / 2));
1921 RHS = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(RHS, RHS,
1922 makeArrayRef(Indices, NumElts / 2));
1923 // Concat the vectors.
1924 // NOTE: Operands have to be swapped to match intrinsic definition.
1925 Rep = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(RHS, LHS,
1926 makeArrayRef(Indices, NumElts));
1927 Rep = Builder.CreateBitCast(Rep, CI->getType());
1928 } else if (IsX86 && Name == "avx512.kand.w") {
1929 Value *LHS = getX86MaskVec(Builder, CI->getArgOperand(0), 16);
1930 Value *RHS = getX86MaskVec(Builder, CI->getArgOperand(1), 16);
1931 Rep = Builder.CreateAnd(LHS, RHS);
1932 Rep = Builder.CreateBitCast(Rep, CI->getType());
1933 } else if (IsX86 && Name == "avx512.kandn.w") {
1934 Value *LHS = getX86MaskVec(Builder, CI->getArgOperand(0), 16);
1935 Value *RHS = getX86MaskVec(Builder, CI->getArgOperand(1), 16);
1936 LHS = Builder.CreateNot(LHS);
1937 Rep = Builder.CreateAnd(LHS, RHS);
1938 Rep = Builder.CreateBitCast(Rep, CI->getType());
1939 } else if (IsX86 && Name == "avx512.kor.w") {
1940 Value *LHS = getX86MaskVec(Builder, CI->getArgOperand(0), 16);
1941 Value *RHS = getX86MaskVec(Builder, CI->getArgOperand(1), 16);
1942 Rep = Builder.CreateOr(LHS, RHS);
1943 Rep = Builder.CreateBitCast(Rep, CI->getType());
1944 } else if (IsX86 && Name == "avx512.kxor.w") {
1945 Value *LHS = getX86MaskVec(Builder, CI->getArgOperand(0), 16);
1946 Value *RHS = getX86MaskVec(Builder, CI->getArgOperand(1), 16);
1947 Rep = Builder.CreateXor(LHS, RHS);
1948 Rep = Builder.CreateBitCast(Rep, CI->getType());
1949 } else if (IsX86 && Name == "avx512.kxnor.w") {
1950 Value *LHS = getX86MaskVec(Builder, CI->getArgOperand(0), 16);
1951 Value *RHS = getX86MaskVec(Builder, CI->getArgOperand(1), 16);
1952 LHS = Builder.CreateNot(LHS);
1953 Rep = Builder.CreateXor(LHS, RHS);
1954 Rep = Builder.CreateBitCast(Rep, CI->getType());
1955 } else if (IsX86 && Name == "avx512.knot.w") {
1956 Rep = getX86MaskVec(Builder, CI->getArgOperand(0), 16);
1957 Rep = Builder.CreateNot(Rep);

3546 const auto &DefaultCase = [&NewFn, &CI]() -> void {
3547 // Handle generic mangling change, but nothing else
3548 assert(
3549 (CI->getCalledFunction()->getName() != NewFn->getName()) &&
3550 "Unknown function for CallInst upgrade and isn't just a name change");
3551 CI->setCalledFunction(NewFn);
3552 };
3553 CallInst *NewCall = nullptr;
3554 switch (NewFn->getIntrinsicID()) {
3555 default: {
3556 DefaultCase();
3557 return;
3558 }
3559 case Intrinsic::experimental_vector_reduce_v2_fmul: {
3560 SmallVector<Value *, 2> Args;
3561 if (CI->isFast())
3562 Args.push_back(ConstantFP::get(CI->getOperand(0)->getType(), 1.0));
3563 else
3564 Args.push_back(CI->getOperand(0));
3565 Args.push_back(CI->getOperand(1));
3566 NewCall = Builder.CreateCall(NewFn, Args);
3567 cast<Instruction>(NewCall)->copyFastMathFlags(CI);
3568 break;
3569 }
3570 case Intrinsic::experimental_vector_reduce_v2_fadd: {
3571 SmallVector<Value *, 2> Args;
3572 if (CI->isFast())
3573 Args.push_back(Constant::getNullValue(CI->getOperand(0)->getType()));
3574 else
3575 Args.push_back(CI->getOperand(0));
3576 Args.push_back(CI->getOperand(1));
3577 NewCall = Builder.CreateCall(NewFn, Args);
3578 cast<Instruction>(NewCall)->copyFastMathFlags(CI);
3579 break;
3580 }
3581 case Intrinsic::arm_neon_vld1:
3582 case Intrinsic::arm_neon_vld2:
3583 case Intrinsic::arm_neon_vld3:
3584 case Intrinsic::arm_neon_vld4:
3585 case Intrinsic::arm_neon_vld2lane:
3586 case Intrinsic::arm_neon_vld3lane:
3587 case Intrinsic::arm_neon_vld4lane:
3588 case Intrinsic::arm_neon_vst1:
3589 case Intrinsic::arm_neon_vst2:
3590 case Intrinsic::arm_neon_vst3:
3591 case Intrinsic::arm_neon_vst4:
3592 case Intrinsic::arm_neon_vst2lane:
3593 case Intrinsic::arm_neon_vst3lane:
3594 case Intrinsic::arm_neon_vst4lane: {
3595 SmallVector<Value *, 4> Args(CI->arg_operands().begin(),
3596 CI->arg_operands().end());
3597 NewCall = Builder.CreateCall(NewFn, Args);
3598 break;
3599 }

3601 case Intrinsic::bitreverse:
3602 NewCall = Builder.CreateCall(NewFn, {CI->getArgOperand(0)});
3603 break;
3604
3605 case Intrinsic::ctlz:
3606 case Intrinsic::cttz:
3607 assert(CI->getNumArgOperands() == 1 &&
3608 "Mismatch between function args and call args");

3615 ? Builder.getFalse()

3618 CI->getNumArgOperands() < 4 ? Builder.getFalse() : CI->getArgOperand(3);
3619 NewCall = Builder.CreateCall(
3620 NewFn, {CI->getArgOperand(0), CI->getArgOperand(1), NullIsUnknownSize, Dynamic});

3630 break;

3634 assert(CI->getNumArgOperands() == 4);

3636 if (auto *Offset = dyn_cast_or_null<Constant>(CI->getArgOperand(1)))
3637 if (Offset->isZeroValue()) {
3638 NewCall = Builder.CreateCall(
3639 NewFn,
3640 {CI->getArgOperand(0), CI->getArgOperand(2), CI->getArgOperand(3)});
3641 break;

3668 // to v2i64. This is purely a nop, since those are bitwise intrinsics.
3669 // So, the only thing required is a bitcast for both arguments.
3670 // First, check the arguments have the old type.
3671 Value *Arg0 = CI->getArgOperand(0);
3672 if (Arg0->getType() != VectorType::get(Type::getFloatTy(C), 4))
3673 return;

3675 // Old intrinsic, add bitcasts
3676 Value *Arg1 = CI->getArgOperand(1);

3678 Type *NewVecTy = VectorType::get(Type::getInt64Ty(C), 2);
3679
3680 Value *BC0 = Builder.CreateBitCast(Arg0, NewVecTy, "cast");
3681 Value *BC1 = Builder.CreateBitCast(Arg1, NewVecTy, "cast");

3683 NewCall = Builder.CreateCall(NewFn, {BC0, BC1});

3688 // This used to take 1 arguments. If we have no arguments, it is already
3689 // upgraded.
3690 if (CI->getNumOperands() == 0)
3691 return;
3692
3693 NewCall = Builder.CreateCall(NewFn);
3694 // Extract the second result and store it.
3695 Value *Data = Builder.CreateExtractValue(NewCall, 1);
3696 // Cast the pointer to the right type.
3697 Value *Ptr = Builder.CreateBitCast(CI->getArgOperand(0),
3698 llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(Data->getType()));
3699 Builder.CreateAlignedStore(Data, Ptr, 1);
3700 // Replace the original call result with the first result of the new call.
3701 Value *TSC = Builder.CreateExtractValue(NewCall, 0);
3702
3703 std::string Name = CI->getName();
3704 if (!Name.empty()) {
3705 CI->setName(Name + ".old");
3706 NewCall->setName(Name);
3707 }
3708 CI->replaceAllUsesWith(TSC);
3709 CI->eraseFromParent();

3720 // an inherently 8-bit immediate operand to these x86 instructions.
3721 SmallVector<Value *, 4> Args(CI->arg_operands().begin(),

3724 // Replace the last argument with a trunc.
3725 Args.back() = Builder.CreateTrunc(Args.back(), Type::getInt8Ty(C), "trunc");

3729
3730 case Intrinsic::thread_pointer: {
3731 NewCall = Builder.CreateCall(NewFn, {});
3732 break;
3733 }
3734
3735 case Intrinsic::invariant_start:
3736 case Intrinsic::invariant_end:
3737 case Intrinsic::masked_load:
3738 case Intrinsic::masked_store:
3739 case Intrinsic::masked_gather:
3740 case Intrinsic::masked_scatter: {
3741 SmallVector<Value *, 4> Args(CI->arg_operands().begin(),
3742 CI->arg_operands().end());
3743 NewCall = Builder.CreateCall(NewFn, Args);
3744 break;
3745 }
3746
3747 case Intrinsic::memcpy:
3748 case Intrinsic::memmove:
3749 case Intrinsic::memset: {
3750 // We have to make sure that the call signature is what we're expecting.
3751 // We only want to change the old signatures by removing the alignment arg:
3752 // @llvm.mem[cpy|move]...(i8*, i8*, i[32|i64], i32, i1)
3753 // -> @llvm.mem[cpy|move]...(i8*, i8*, i[32|i64], i1)
3754 // @llvm.memset...(i8*, i8, i[32|64], i32, i1)
3755 // -> @llvm.memset...(i8*, i8, i[32|64], i1)
3756 // Note: i8*'s in the above can be any pointer type
3757 if (CI->getNumArgOperands() != 5) {
3758 DefaultCase();
3759 return;
3760 }
3761 // Remove alignment argument (3), and add alignment attributes to the
3762 // dest/src pointers.
3763 Value *Args[4] = {CI->getArgOperand(0), CI->getArgOperand(1),
3764 CI->getArgOperand(2), CI->getArgOperand(4)};
3765 NewCall = Builder.CreateCall(NewFn, Args);
3766 auto *MemCI = cast<MemIntrinsic>(NewCall);
3767 // All mem intrinsics support dest alignment.
3768 const ConstantInt *Align = cast<ConstantInt>(CI->getArgOperand(3));
3769 MemCI->setDestAlignment(Align->getZExtValue());
3770 // Memcpy/Memmove also support source alignment.
3771 if (auto *MTI = dyn_cast<MemTransferInst>(MemCI))
3772 MTI->setSourceAlignment(Align->getZExtValue());
3773 break;
3774 }
3775 }
3776 assert(NewCall && "Should have either set this variable or returned through "
3777 "the default case");
3778 std::string Name = CI->getName();
3779 if (!Name.empty()) {
3780 CI->setName(Name + ".old");
3781 NewCall->setName(Name);
3782 }
3783 CI->replaceAllUsesWith(NewCall);
3784 CI->eraseFromParent();
3785}
3786
3787void llvm::UpgradeCallsToIntrinsic(Function *F) {
3788 assert(F && "Illegal attempt to upgrade a non-existent intrinsic.");
3789
3790 // Check if this function should be upgraded and get the replacement function
3791 // if there is one.
3792 Function *NewFn;
3793 if (UpgradeIntrinsicFunction(F, NewFn)) {
3794 // Replace all users of the old function with the new function or new
3795 // instructions. This is not a range loop because the call is deleted.
3796 for (auto UI = F->user_begin(), UE = F->user_end(); UI != UE; )
3797 if (CallInst *CI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(*UI++))
3798 UpgradeIntrinsicCall(CI, NewFn);
3799
3800 // Remove old function, no longer used, from the module.
3801 F->eraseFromParent();
3802 }
3803}

3805MDNode *llvm::UpgradeTBAANode(MDNode &MD) {
3806 // Check if the tag uses struct-path aware TBAA format.
3807 if (isa<MDNode>(MD.getOperand(0)) && MD.getNumOperands() >= 3)
3808 return &MD;
3809
3810 auto &Context = MD.getContext();
3811 if (MD.getNumOperands() == 3) {
3812 Metadata *Elts[] = {MD.getOperand(0), MD.getOperand(1)};
3813 MDNode *ScalarType = MDNode::get(Context, Elts);
3814 // Create a MDNode <ScalarType, ScalarType, offset 0, const>
3815 Metadata *Elts2[] = {ScalarType, ScalarType,
3816 ConstantAsMetadata::get(
3817 Constant::getNullValue(Type::getInt64Ty(Context))),
3818 MD.getOperand(2)};
3819 return MDNode::get(Context, Elts2);
3820 }
3821 // Create a MDNode <MD, MD, offset 0>
3822 Metadata *Elts[] = {&MD, &MD, ConstantAsMetadata::get(Constant::getNullValue(
3823 Type::getInt64Ty(Context)))};
3824 return MDNode::get(Context, Elts);
3825}

3827Instruction *llvm::UpgradeBitCastInst(unsigned Opc, Value *V, Type *DestTy,
3828 Instruction *&Temp) {
3829 if (Opc != Instruction::BitCast)
3830 return nullptr;
3831
3832 Temp = nullptr;
3833 Type *SrcTy = V->getType();
3834 if (SrcTy->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy() && DestTy->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy() &&
3835 SrcTy->getPointerAddressSpace() != DestTy->getPointerAddressSpace()) {
3836 LLVMContext &Context = V->getContext();
3837
3838 // We have no information about target data layout, so we assume that
3839 // the maximum pointer size is 64bit.
3840 Type *MidTy = Type::getInt64Ty(Context);
3841 Temp = CastInst::Create(Instruction::PtrToInt, V, MidTy);
3842
3843 return CastInst::Create(Instruction::IntToPtr, Temp, DestTy);
3844 }
3845
3846 return nullptr;
3847}
3848
3849Value *llvm::UpgradeBitCastExpr(unsigned Opc, Constant *C, Type *DestTy) {
3850 if (Opc != Instruction::BitCast)
3851 return nullptr;
3852
3853 Type *SrcTy = C->getType();
3854 if (SrcTy->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy() && DestTy->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy() &&
3855 SrcTy->getPointerAddressSpace() != DestTy->getPointerAddressSpace()) {
3856 LLVMContext &Context = C->getContext();
3857
3858 // We have no information about target data layout, so we assume that
3859 // the maximum pointer size is 64bit.
3860 Type *MidTy = Type::getInt64Ty(Context);
3861
3862 return ConstantExpr::getIntToPtr(ConstantExpr::getPtrToInt(C, MidTy),
3863 DestTy);
3864 }
3865
3866 return nullptr;
3867}

3869/// Check the debug info version number, if it is out-dated, drop the debug
3870/// info. Return true if module is modified.
3871bool llvm::UpgradeDebugInfo(Module &M) {
3872 unsigned Version = getDebugMetadataVersionFromModule(M);
3873 if (Version == DEBUG_METADATA_VERSION) {
3874 bool BrokenDebugInfo = false;
3875 if (verifyModule(M, &llvm::errs(), &BrokenDebugInfo))
3876 report_fatal_error("Broken module found, compilation aborted!");
3877 if (!BrokenDebugInfo)
3878 // Everything is ok.
3879 return false;
3880 else {
3881 // Diagnose malformed debug info.
3882 DiagnosticInfoIgnoringInvalidDebugMetadata Diag(M);
3883 M.getContext().diagnose(Diag);
3884 }
3885 }
3886 bool Modified = StripDebugInfo(M);
3887 if (Modified && Version != DEBUG_METADATA_VERSION) {
3888 // Diagnose a version mismatch.
3889 DiagnosticInfoDebugMetadataVersion DiagVersion(M, Version);
3890 M.getContext().diagnose(DiagVersion);
3891 }
3892 return Modified;
3893}

3895bool llvm::UpgradeRetainReleaseMarker(Module &M) {
3896 bool Changed = false;
3897 const char *MarkerKey = "clang.arc.retainAutoreleasedReturnValueMarker";
3898 NamedMDNode *ModRetainReleaseMarker = M.getNamedMetadata(MarkerKey);
3899 if (ModRetainReleaseMarker) {
3900 MDNode *Op = ModRetainReleaseMarker->getOperand(0);
3901 if (Op) {
3902 MDString *ID = dyn_cast_or_null<MDString>(Op->getOperand(0));
3903 if (ID) {
3904 SmallVector<StringRef, 4> ValueComp;
3905 ID->getString().split(ValueComp, "#");
3906 if (ValueComp.size() == 2) {
3907 std::string NewValue = ValueComp[0].str() + ";" + ValueComp[1].str();
3908 ID = MDString::get(M.getContext(), NewValue);
3909 }
3910 M.addModuleFlag(Module::Error, MarkerKey, ID);
3911 M.eraseNamedMetadata(ModRetainReleaseMarker);
3912 Changed = true;
3913 }
3914 }
3915 }
3916 return Changed;
3917}

3919bool llvm::UpgradeModuleFlags(Module &M) {
3920 NamedMDNode *ModFlags = M.getModuleFlagsMetadata();
3921 if (!ModFlags)
3922 return false;
3923
3924 bool HasObjCFlag = false, HasClassProperties = false, Changed = false;
3925 for (unsigned I = 0, E = ModFlags->getNumOperands(); I != E; ++I) {
3926 MDNode *Op = ModFlags->getOperand(I);
3927 if (Op->getNumOperands() != 3)
3928 continue;
3929 MDString *ID = dyn_cast_or_null<MDString>(Op->getOperand(1));
3930 if (!ID)
3931 continue;
3932 if (ID->getString() == "Objective-C Image Info Version")
3933 HasObjCFlag = true;
3934 if (ID->getString() == "Objective-C Class Properties")
3935 HasClassProperties = true;
3936 // Upgrade PIC/PIE Module Flags. The module flag behavior for these two
3937 // field was Error and now they are Max.
3938 if (ID->getString() == "PIC Level" || ID->getString() == "PIE Level") {
3939 if (auto *Behavior =
3940 mdconst::dyn_extract_or_null<ConstantInt>(Op->getOperand(0))) {
3941 if (Behavior->getLimitedValue() == Module::Error) {
3942 Type *Int32Ty = Type::getInt32Ty(M.getContext());
3943 Metadata *Ops[3] = {
3944 ConstantAsMetadata::get(ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, Module::Max)),
3945 MDString::get(M.getContext(), ID->getString()),
3946 Op->getOperand(2)};
3947 ModFlags->setOperand(I, MDNode::get(M.getContext(), Ops));
3948 Changed = true;
3949 }
3950 }
3951 }
3952 // Upgrade Objective-C Image Info Section. Removed the whitespce in the
3953 // section name so that llvm-lto will not complain about mismatching
3954 // module flags that is functionally the same.
3955 if (ID->getString() == "Objective-C Image Info Section") {
3956 if (auto *Value = dyn_cast_or_null<MDString>(Op->getOperand(2))) {
3957 SmallVector<StringRef, 4> ValueComp;
3958 Value->getString().split(ValueComp, " ");
3959 if (ValueComp.size() != 1) {
3960 std::string NewValue;
3961 for (auto &S : ValueComp)
3962 NewValue += S.str();
3963 Metadata *Ops[3] = {Op->getOperand(0), Op->getOperand(1),
3964 MDString::get(M.getContext(), NewValue)};
3965 ModFlags->setOperand(I, MDNode::get(M.getContext(), Ops));
3966 Changed = true;
3967 }
3968 }
3969 }
3970 }
3971
3972 // "Objective-C Class Properties" is recently added for Objective-C. We
3973 // upgrade ObjC bitcodes to contain a "Objective-C Class Properties" module
3974 // flag of value 0, so we can correclty downgrade this flag when trying to
3975 // link an ObjC bitcode without this module flag with an ObjC bitcode with
3976 // this module flag.
3977 if (HasObjCFlag && !HasClassProperties) {
3978 M.addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Override, "Objective-C Class Properties",
3979 (uint32_t)0);
3980 Changed = true;
3981 }
3982
3983 return Changed;
3984}

3986void llvm::UpgradeSectionAttributes(Module &M) {
3987 auto TrimSpaces = [](StringRef Section) -> std::string {
3988 SmallVector<StringRef, 5> Components;
3989 Section.split(Components, ',');
3990
3991 SmallString<32> Buffer;
3992 raw_svector_ostream OS(Buffer);
3993
3994 for (auto Component : Components)
3995 OS << ',' << Component.trim();
3996
3997 return OS.str().substr(1);
3998 };
3999
4000 for (auto &GV : M.globals()) {
4001 if (!GV.hasSection())
4002 continue;
4003
4004 StringRef Section = GV.getSection();
4005
4006 if (!Section.startswith("__DATA, __objc_catlist"))
4007 continue;
4008
4009 // __DATA, __objc_catlist, regular, no_dead_strip
4010 // __DATA,__objc_catlist,regular,no_dead_strip
4011 GV.setSection(TrimSpaces(Section));
4012 }
4013}

4015static bool isOldLoopArgument(Metadata *MD) {
4016 auto *T = dyn_cast_or_null<MDTuple>(MD);
4017 if (!T)
4018 return false;
4019 if (T->getNumOperands() < 1)
4020 return false;
4021 auto *S = dyn_cast_or_null<MDString>(T->getOperand(0));
4022 if (!S)
4023 return false;
4024 return S->getString().startswith("llvm.vectorizer.");
4025}

4027static MDString *upgradeLoopTag(LLVMContext &C, StringRef OldTag) {
4028 StringRef OldPrefix = "llvm.vectorizer.";
4029 assert(OldTag.startswith(OldPrefix) && "Expected old prefix");
4030
4031 if (OldTag == "llvm.vectorizer.unroll")
4032 return MDString::get(C, "llvm.loop.interleave.count");
4033
4034 return MDString::get(
4035 C, (Twine("llvm.loop.vectorize.") + OldTag.drop_front(OldPrefix.size()))
4036 .str());
4037}
4038
4039static Metadata *upgradeLoopArgument(Metadata *MD) {
4040 auto *T = dyn_cast_or_null<MDTuple>(MD);
4041 if (!T)
4042 return MD;
4043 if (T->getNumOperands() < 1)
4044 return MD;
4045 auto *OldTag = dyn_cast_or_null<MDString>(T->getOperand(0));
4046 if (!OldTag)
4047 return MD;
4048 if (!OldTag->getString().startswith("llvm.vectorizer."))
4049 return MD;
4050
4051 // This has an old tag. Upgrade it.
4052 SmallVector<Metadata *, 8> Ops;
4053 Ops.reserve(T->getNumOperands());
4054 Ops.push_back(upgradeLoopTag(T->getContext(), OldTag->getString()));
4055 for (unsigned I = 1, E = T->getNumOperands(); I != E; ++I)
4056 Ops.push_back(T->getOperand(I));
4057
4058 return MDTuple::get(T->getContext(), Ops);
4059}
4060
4061MDNode *llvm::upgradeInstructionLoopAttachment(MDNode &N) {
4062 auto *T = dyn_cast<MDTuple>(&N);
4063 if (!T)
4064 return &N;
4065
4066 if (none_of(T->operands(), isOldLoopArgument))
4067 return &N;
4068
4069 SmallVector<Metadata *, 8> Ops;
4070 Ops.reserve(T->getNumOperands());
4071 for (Metadata *MD : T->operands())
4072 Ops.push_back(upgradeLoopArgument(MD));
4073
4074 return MDTuple::get(T->getContext(), Ops);
4075}
